020import gov.nist.secauto.metaschema.databind.model.annotations.BoundAssembly;

029import org.apache.commons.lang3.builder.ReflectionToStringBuilder;

032import java.math.BigInteger;
033import java.util.LinkedList;
034import java.util.List;

036@SuppressWarnings({
037    "PMD.DataClass",
038    "PMD.FieldNamingConventions"
039})
040@MetaschemaAssembly(
041    formalName = "Targeted Cardinality Constraint",
042    name = "targeted-has-cardinality-constraint",
043    moduleClass = MetaschemaModelModule.class)
044public class TargetedHasCardinalityConstraint implements IBoundObject, ITargetedConstraintBase {
045  private final IMetaschemaData __metaschemaData;
046
047  @BoundFlag(
048      formalName = "Constraint Identifier",
049      name = "id",
050      typeAdapter = TokenAdapter.class)
051  private String _id;
052
053  @BoundFlag(
054      formalName = "Constraint Severity Level",
055      name = "level",
056      defaultValue = "ERROR",
057      typeAdapter = TokenAdapter.class,
058      valueConstraints = @ValueConstraints(allowedValues = @AllowedValues(level = IConstraint.Level.ERROR, values = {
059          @AllowedValue(value = "CRITICAL",
060              description = "A violation of the constraint represents a serious fault in the content that will prevent typical use of the content."),
061          @AllowedValue(value = "ERROR",
062              description = "A violation of the constraint represents a fault in the content. This may include issues around compatibility, integrity, consistency, etc."),
063          @AllowedValue(value = "WARNING",
064              description = "A violation of the constraint represents a potential issue with the content."),
065          @AllowedValue(value = "INFORMATIONAL",
066              description = "A violation of the constraint represents a point of interest."),
067          @AllowedValue(value = "DEBUG",
068              description = "A violation of the constraint represents a fault in the content that may warrant review by a developer when performing model or tool development.") })))
069  private String _level;
070
071  @BoundFlag(
072      formalName = "Minimum Occurrence",
073      name = "min-occurs",
074      typeAdapter = NonNegativeIntegerAdapter.class)
075  private BigInteger _minOccurs;
076
077  @BoundFlag(
078      formalName = "Maximum Occurrence",
079      name = "max-occurs",
080      typeAdapter = StringAdapter.class,
081      valueConstraints = @ValueConstraints(
082          matches = @Matches(level = IConstraint.Level.ERROR, pattern = "^[1-9][0-9]*|unbounded$")))
083  private String _maxOccurs;
084
085  @BoundFlag(
086      formalName = "Constraint Target Metapath Expression",
087      name = "target",
088      required = true,
089      typeAdapter = StringAdapter.class)
090  private String _target;
091
092  @BoundField(
093      formalName = "Formal Name",
094      description = "A formal name for the data construct, to be presented in documentation.",
095      useName = "formal-name")
096  private String _formalName;
097
098  @BoundField(
099      formalName = "Description",
100      description = "A short description of the data construct's purpose, describing the constructs semantics.",
101      useName = "description",
102      typeAdapter = MarkupLineAdapter.class)
103  private MarkupLine _description;
104
105  @BoundAssembly(
106      formalName = "Property",
107      useName = "prop",
108      maxOccurs = -1,
109      groupAs = @GroupAs(name = "props", inJson = JsonGroupAsBehavior.LIST))
110  private List<Property> _props;
111
112  @BoundField(
113      formalName = "Remarks",
114      description = "Any explanatory or helpful information to be provided about the remarks parent.",
115      useName = "remarks")
116  private Remarks _remarks;
117
118  public TargetedHasCardinalityConstraint() {
119    this(null);
120  }
121
122  public TargetedHasCardinalityConstraint(IMetaschemaData data) {
123    this.__metaschemaData = data;
124  }
125
126  @Override
127  public IMetaschemaData getMetaschemaData() {
128    return __metaschemaData;
129  }
130
131  @Override
132  public String getId() {
133    return _id;
134  }
135
136  public void setId(String value) {
137    _id = value;
138  }
139
140  @Override
141  public String getLevel() {
142    return _level;
143  }
144
145  public void setLevel(String value) {
146    _level = value;
147  }
148
149  public BigInteger getMinOccurs() {
150    return _minOccurs;
151  }
152
153  public void setMinOccurs(BigInteger value) {
154    _minOccurs = value;
155  }
156
157  public String getMaxOccurs() {
158    return _maxOccurs;
159  }
160
161  public void setMaxOccurs(String value) {
162    _maxOccurs = value;
163  }
164
165  @Override
166  public String getTarget() {
167    return _target;
168  }
169
170  public void setTarget(String value) {
171    _target = value;
172  }
173
174  @Override
175  public String getFormalName() {
176    return _formalName;
177  }
178
179  public void setFormalName(String value) {
180    _formalName = value;
181  }
182
183  @Override
184  public MarkupLine getDescription() {
185    return _description;
186  }
187
188  public void setDescription(MarkupLine value) {
189    _description = value;
190  }
191
192  @Override
193  public List<Property> getProps() {
194    return _props;
195  }
196
197  public void setProps(List<Property> value) {
198    _props = value;
199  }
200
201  /**
202   * Add a new {@link Property} item to the underlying collection.
203   *
204   * @param item
205   *          the item to add
206   * @return {@code true}
207   */
208  public boolean addProp(Property item) {
209    Property value = ObjectUtils.requireNonNull(item, "item cannot be null");
210    if (_props == null) {
211      _props = new LinkedList<>();
212    }
213    return _props.add(value);
214  }
215
216  /**
217   * Remove the first matching {@link Property} item from the underlying
218   * collection.
219   *
220   * @param item
221   *          the item to remove
222   * @return {@code true} if the item was removed or {@code false} otherwise
223   */
224  public boolean removeProp(Property item) {
225    Property value = ObjectUtils.requireNonNull(item, "item cannot be null");
226    return _props != null && _props.remove(value);
227  }
228
229  @Override
230  public Remarks getRemarks() {
231    return _remarks;
232  }
233
234  public void setRemarks(Remarks value) {
235    _remarks = value;
236  }
237
238  @Override
239  public String toString() {
240    return new ReflectionToStringBuilder(this, ToStringStyle.MULTI_LINE_STYLE).toString();
241  }
242}
